A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Advanced Capabilities for Missile Enhancement (ACME) program supports enhancements to ICBM operations. More information is available at higher classification
levels.

 In FY2026, BPAC 675920, Next Generation Reentry Capabilities (NGRC) encompassed efforts to design, develop, produce, and deploy new payload system suites
 (reentry vehicles and/or capabilities)
 In FY2027, BPAC 675920 was renamed Advanced Capability for Missile Enhancement (ACME)
 NGRC funding stayed within BPAC 675920.

 FY2027 continues to support the enabling functions of ACME to include but is not limited to Prime support and studies, engineering support, security support, direct
 program support costs and information technology.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program
 funds would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program element 0605827F, 0605828F, 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605832F, 0605833F, 0605898F,
 0606398F.

