A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The program office is developing and prototyping the Resilient Missile Warning Tracking (MWT) MEO (Project 657MEO) for Guardians across Missile Warning and
Missile Tracking (MW/MT) mission area. As a result, the Service will advance space-based technology associated with Golden Dome, and deter, neutralize, defeat and/
or destroy counterspace threats and defend the homeland.

 A new class of threat requires a new class of architecture. Since legacy systems alone cannot maintain custody of advanced, dim and maneuverable missile threats,
 Resilient MWT delivers a multi-orbit architecture designed to defeat new threats, support homeland defense, Combatant Command operations and the broader missile
 defense kill chain. The United States Space Force Space Systems Command and Space Development Agency are collaborating to deliver Overhead Persistent
 Infrared capabilities, in concert with Department of War and Intelligence Community partners, to support a proliferated space architecture that is resilient by design and
 capable of operating through contested environments. Resilient Missile Warning and Tracking - Medium Earth Orbit space and ground efforts pivot the Department
 of the Air Force's legacy missile warning force design to a more resilient multi-orbit approach to counter advanced missiles, hypersonic glide vehicles, and fractional
 orbital bombardment threats. Resilient Missile Warning and Tracking Medium Earth Orbit was originally anchored in Missile Warning and Missile Defense Capability
 Development Document requirements validated by the Joint Requirements Oversight Council; there is now a Joint Requirement Oversight Council-approved Capability
 Development Document Annex with very specific Medium Earth Orbit and Low Earth Orbit requirements. Constellation resiliency is foundational to the Department of the
 Air Force's Resilient Missile Warning and Tracking force design, therefore, the Overhead Persistent Infrared Family of Systems, including Missile Warning and Tracking
 Medium Earth Orbit, is designed to work cohesively to gain and maintain custody of a spectrum of missile threats.

 This program falls within the Missile Warning and Missile Tracking (MW/MT) mission area which provides the multi-orbit space and ground architecture required to detect
 and track missiles and hypersonic glide vehicles worldwide. Space Force investment program interdependencies include:
 RDT&E Budget Line Items: Missile Defense Radars (1203873SF); Ballistic Missile EW Systems (1203909SF); Joint Tactical Ground System (1208053SF); NCMC - TW/
 AA System (1203906SF); Next - Generation OPIR (1206442SF); Next - Generation - GEO (1206443SF); Next - Generation - Ground (1206440SF); Next - Generation
 - Polar (1206444SF); NUDET Detection System (1203913SF); Resilient MW / MT - LEO (1206446SF); Resilient MW / MT - MEO (1206447SF) and elements of
 Procurement Budget Line Item: Space Mods (SPCMOD).

 The Medium Earth Orbit program will deploy space assets in multiple Epochs to allow for incremental capability delivery and to ensure competition throughout the
 lifecycle of the program. Resilient Missile Warning and Tracking Medium Earth Orbit will bolster legacy Space Based Infrared Satellite and Next-Gen Overhead
 Persistent Infrared capabilities and will independently satisfy mission area Capability Development Document requirements for missile tracking by as early as FY


