C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Description: This activity funds development of Medium Earth Orbit space vehicles, with two launches planned to deliver twelve
space vehicles by FY 2028, and ground efforts with operations necessary to deliver initial capability for the combined Low Earth
Orbit and Medium Earth Orbit architecture. Initial capability consists of regional tracking, mission management and control, and
coordinated regional warning and tracking access validated through on-orbit measurements. After performance validation is
complete, prototype sensors will feed data directly to operational warning and defense systems. Furthermore, the initial capability
will provide sensitivity to detect emerging threats, accurate tracking to contain maneuvering targets, and mission data delivery
within required latency timelines to close the kill-chain. Initial Warfighter Capability is now defined in the Overhead Persistent
Infrared Resilient Medium Earth Orbit/Low Earth Orbit Capability Development Document Annex as global missile tracking access
and will be provided in Epoch 2.

Data Fusion: Test, assess, and validate sensor performance on the ground and on-orbit to ensure track data is integrated by
program of record data fusion operational programs such as Future Operationally Resilient Ground Evolution (FORGE) (PE
1206440SF), Ballistic Missile Defense Overhead Persistent Infrared Architecture (BOA), other classified partners and missions,
research and development multi-intelligence fusion (PE 1206442SF), and intelligence characterization. Space Vehicle testing
is on contract as of December 2022. Fusion software studies underway with Future Operationally Resilient Ground Evolution
(FORGE) program as of March 2023. Additional early integration support and studies with BOA started in FY 2024. In FY 2025,
sensor models began to support future modeling and simulation activities with the Future Operationally Resilient Ground Evolution
(FORGE) and Missile Defense program offices.

FY 2026 Plans:
Space: Crucial deliveries of payloads and satellite buses from the remaining contractor for integration and assembly. The vendor
intends to deliver flight payloads and satellite buses for the first six satellites and begin space vehicle level assembly, integration
and testing. Millennium Space Systems will initiate assembling and testing space vehicles 7-12 to complete two orbital planes of
capability. They will complete launch vehicle integration studies and launch vehicle selection for both launches, and support first
launch no earlier than the end of 3Q FY 2027.

Ground: Contractor will complete software builds for both command and control and mission data processing; The MEO Space
Operations Center (MSOC) fit up at the Boulder Ground Innovation Facility (BGIF) will be completed and the operations floor
will be prepared for launch rehearsals. The Ground Entry Point (GEP) contractor will complete Integration, test, validation, and
verification in preparation for launch rehearsals and Launch and Early On-Orbit Test campaign. Ground antenna initialization and
system end to end testing at the BGIF, Schriever Space Force Base, Al Udeid Air Base, Clear Space Force Station, and other
associated antennas will be completed in FY 2026.



