C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Data Fusion: Finalize verification and validation campaigns to ensure the fidelity of the models are adequate to be integrated into
enterprise sensor test campaigns spanning the entire Overhead Persistent Infrared architecture. In FY 2026, major simulation and
ground test campaign planning will occur to ensure sensor models and live on-orbit data will be ingested at the appropriate missile
warning and missile defense test events occurring in FY 2026-2027. Work with data fusion programs (FORGE, BOA, Persistent
Unified Messaging Architecture) to ensure on-orbit data is timely and accurate.
FY 2027 Plans:
Space: Final testing and integration of flight payloads and satellite buses for Plane 1. These events will culminate in satellite
shipment to launch site at Cape Canaveral and initial launch capability. Immediately following launch, Millennium Space Systems
will conduct early orbit checkout and testing procedures. The vendor will then conduct operational testing of the full orbital plane
of satellites. In addition, Epoch 1 will be going through assembly, integration and testing of Plane 2 in preparation for a second
launch and on-orbit test campaign beginning in mid to late FY 2028.

Ground: Conduct site configuration and instrumentation efforts, including RF interference testing, installation of hardware, system
integration, and execute engineering support during developmental testing and implement corrective actions, through the use of
a deficiency reporting list, resulting from developmental testing at GEP sites at Schriever Space Force Base, Al Udeid Air Base,
and Clear Space Force Station, as well as the MEO Space Operations Center (MSOC) located at the Boulder Ground Innovation
Facility (BGIF).
