INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0203345F$$, 2027, $$The DAF Operations Security (OPSEC) Program enables the effective and efficient execution of the OPSEC process. OPSEC is a Presidentially directed security
discipline and operational function that denies adversaries the ability to collect, analyze, and exploit information that might provide an advantage against the United
States by preventing the compromise of critical information through a process of continual assessment that identifies and analyzes critical information, vulnerabilities,
risks, and external threats.

 OPSEC requires the continual implementation and modernization of measures and countermeasures, to include technical solutions, to mitigate operational risk. The
 Battering Ram project and associated efforts, may include but are not limited to, provide the automated classification governance, requirements management, and
 scaling across the Department of War (DoW) through the modernization of the information security classification and declassification processes which enhance critical
 OPSEC measures; thereby reducing risks to DOW and DAF capabilities and missions.

 The Battering Ram project is developing and implementing the information technology infrastructure that enables the modernization of existing information security
 capabilities to realize a uniform system for classifying, safeguarding, and declassifying national security information as prescribed in Executive Order 13526, Classified
 National Security Information. Battering Ram will enable the DoW to improve warfighter effectiveness by increasing the speed with which information can be exchanged
 by reducing complex and manual review processes and providing a secure multi-level information system and information technology infrastructure to support the
 execution and operation of the information security enterprise.

 Battering Ram will continue to operationalize capabilities that further the DoW's ability to centrally manage classification, such as but not limited to:

 - Digitizing, curating, and maintaining authoritative classification and declassification guidance across all classification levels (CUI through TS//SCI/SAR)

 - Automatically classifying and validating existing DoW documents and data using machine-readable guidance and Artificial Intelligence (AI)-enabled decision support

 - Providing software services to both connected and air-gapped DoW and cleared contractor information systems

Operational Systems Development

 - Enabling adjudication, governance, and continuous improvement of classification policy through a centralized digital infrastructure

 Battering Ram directly supports mission assurance, operational security, information advantage, and risk reduction by replacing fragmented, manual, and inconsistent
 classification processes with a standardized, auditable, and automated digital lifecycle.

 This program element may include all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would
 be in addition to the civilian pay expense budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 06050831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

 This program is in Budget Activity 7, Operational System Development because this budget activity includes development efforts to upgrade systems that have been
 fielded or have received approval for full rate production and anticipate production funding in the current or subsequent fiscal year.$$, $$The DAF Operations Security (OPSEC) Program enables the effective and efficient execution of the OPSEC process. OPSEC is a Presidentially directed security
