Description: In compliance with M-Code Mandate Public Law 111-383, EGI-M will provide an M-Code compliant, anti-spoofing
PNT solution to prevent exploitation of the weapon system by adversaries, enable more accurate tracking of GPS satellites, and
support a more secure and flexible cryptography architecture.

This effort covers the M-Code Weapons product line and EGI-M integration, test, software, and hardware necessary to ensure the
F-22's ability to employ M-Code configured weapons and field the EGI-M. The Air Force Weapons Program Office is scheduled to
field M-Code- enabled weapons prior to the availability of an M-Code GPS solution for the F-22.

Starting in the 27 PB, Operational Flight Program (OFP) software was transitioned to the SPEED major thrust for FY2026 and
FY2027.

