Title: Hybrid SATCOM                                                                                                                    0.000        13.684          45.240
Description: Hybrid SATCOM is an F-15EX multi-band SATCOM solution that leverages terminal and aperture capabilities
developed in Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) PE 0604003F, eliminating duplication of effort and optimizing
capability delivery in alignment with the DAF BATTLE NETWORK architecture.

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
Begin non-recurring engineering (NRE) and integration development efforts on multiple contracts to develop and integrate multi-
band apertures and terminals with aircraft systems. Modify aircraft software (Operational Flight Program) to enable integration and
data sharing in accordance with DAF Battle Network architecture leveraging other Long Range Kill Chain (LRKC) demos.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue non-recurring engineering (NRE) and integration development efforts on multiple contracts to develop and integrate
multi-band apertures and terminals with aircraft systems. Modify aircraft software (Operational Flight Program) to enable
integration and data sharing in accordance with DAF Battle Network architecture leveraging other Long Range Kill Chain (LRKC)
demos. Continue software integration allowing for adjunct processor capability while beginning install for test jets.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Additional funding for continued non-recurring engineering and beginning of test jet installs
Title: F-15EX Development & Test                                                                                                        54.875      54.031         73.960
Description: F-15EX RDT&E funding continues capability development and test efforts, as well as integration of long-range kill
chain (LRKC) weapons. LRKC development efforts provide the F-15EX responsive, long-range strike capabilities against time-
critical or heavily defended targets and Offensive Counter-Air/Defensive Counter-Air (OCA/DCA) mission sets.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue cybersecurity test events. Continue non-recurring engineering (NRE) and integration development efforts, including
continued Flight Control Computer (FCC) and other DMSMS redesign development needed to continue production line deliveries.
Continue software development integration efforts, including merging F-15EX-unique software into the common F-15 OFP.
Continue upgrading existing F-15 training systems and systems integration labs for F-15EX-unique capabilities. Provide program
support to manage and execute F-15EX efforts.

Long-Range Kill Chain (LRKC) development and integration efforts require updates to the Operational Flight Program.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue cybersecurity test events. Continue non-recurring engineering (NRE) and integration development efforts, including
continued Flight Control Computer (FCC) and other DMSMS redesign development needed to continue production line deliveries.
Continue software development integration efforts, including merging F-15EX-unique software into the common F-15 OFP.
Continue upgrading existing F-15 training systems and systems integration labs for F-15EX-unique capabilities. Provide program
support to manage and execute F-15EX efforts.

Operational Systems Development

