FY 2026 Plans:
Executed System Improvement Program (SIP) to continually advance capability of the weapon and transition
program to a steady OFP update cycle, executed under agile development. Continue to perform Operational
Flight Program (OFP) software and firmware updates to integrate new Military-Code (M-Code) GPS receiver and
forward and aft electronics upgrades into the SDB II GBU-53A/B Configuration 2 All Up Round (AUR) weapon.
Integrated CCA stack design verification testing and qualification to support Configuration 2 AUR integration and
qualification. Integrated and test of the TacNet 1.5 weapons data link (WDL) with the new CCAs and associated
OFP changes.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continue integrated CCA stack design verification testing and qualification to support Configuration 2 AUR
integration and qualification. Continue integration and test of the TacNet 1.5 WDL with the new CCAs and
associated OFP changes.

Continue development, qualification, and testing of engineering changes associated with platform integration,
program protection, exportability, cyber security, enhanced lethality, survivability, anti-jam and anti-spoof
capabilities, threat defeat, software-based capability enhancements, obsolescence, and affordability.

Procure developmental test assets to support developmental qualification and testing, as required. Conduct
developmental Captive Flight Tests, platform integration testing, and flight test shots. Continue integration of
SDB II with Command and Control Infrastructure, including AOC integration and JTAC kits. Continue technical
order updates to support ongoing OFP development efforts. Continue BRU-61 OFP updates and integration.
Conduct trade studies and concept development for technology refresh redesigns as required based on
obsolescence forecasts.
