E. Acquisition Strategy
October 2009, one contractor was selected in April 2010 and awarded the EMD contract in August 2010. The EMD contract is a Fixed-Price Incentive Firm (FPIF)
contract to execute weapon development and qualification and threshold platform integration and test with priced production options for the first five production lots.
SDB II production Lots 1-3 were FPIF. Production Lots 4-5 were firm fixed price, and Lots 6-11 are FPIF. The Government is buying the SDB II GBU-53 based on the
contractor System Performance Specification (SPS), which has been approved by the Government. The contractor is accountable for system performance as defined
in the SPS and a system warranty as defined in the EMD contract and follow-on production contracts. Accordingly, the contractor is accountable to the Government for
the design of the weapon system, as well as the planning and execution of the Development Test and Evaluation (DT&E) program to verify system performance. The
Government formally arranges and funds the use of Government flight test support for DT&E and OT&E.

In September 2017, the Government awarded the incremental Engineering Change Proposal (iECP) sole source indefinite delivery indefinite quantity (IDIQ) contract
to Raytheon Missile Systems to design, develop, integrate, model, test, and qualify engineering changes to SDB II baseline hardware and software to meet emerging
threats and to maintain compatibility with external systems. In April 2020, the Government added the flexible Lot Integration and Test (LIT) contract deliver order with
pre-priced scope to conduct AUR-level qualification and testing of new hardware configurations. Activities for this IDIQ include, but are not limited to, M-Code GPS
development, data link cryptographic modernization, program protection, exportability features, cyber security, advanced guidance, navigation and control, enhanced
lethality, and address obsolescence issues and affordability opportunities as well as required weapon qualification and testing activities.




