integration of joint fires, and other critical mission areas required for integrated Tactical Air Control Party/Air Support Operations Center (TACP/ASOC) Command and
Control (C2) mission success. At the completion of the technology validation, a contract will be competitively awarded to complete JTAGSS development, deployment
and integration. Current software is Government or Commercial Off-the-Shelf technologies (GOTS/COTS) allowing almost any training technology development
company to compete, which lowers technical risk, schedule risk, and cost.

