INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0207452F$$, 2027, $$Deliberate and Crisis Action Planning and Execution System (DCAPES) is the Department of the Air Force (DAF) classified Command and Control (C2) National
Security System (NSS) used to implement the Air Force Force Generation (AFFORGEN) process and project forces (includes weapon systems, logistics, and
personnel). It enables the DAF to posture mission ready and equipped forces (organized in effects-based operational capability packages) to deliver air, space, and
cyberspace capabilities to Joint commanders worldwide. DCAPES supports joint, combined, and DAF military operations worldwide.

FY 2027 funding will be used to support the continued development of capabilities within the DCAPES system. These efforts will enhance the Shortfall Management
Module which enables units to report and route manpower deficiencies to appropriate command level for resolution. The funding will also be used to develop the
Manpower Analysis Tool used to analyze and inform personnel planning and prevent future shortfalls.

The FY 2027 funding continues to enhance the functionality of the system, crucial in supporting war planning, and will be executed against capabilities packaged into
agile development projects for multiple releases based on warfighter priorities.

This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.$$, $$Deliberate and Crisis Action Planning and Execution System (DCAPES) is the Department of the Air Force (DAF) classified Command and Control (C2) National
Security System (NSS) used to implement the Air Force Force Generation (AFFORGEN) process and project forces (includes weapon systems, logistics, and
personnel). It enables the DAF to posture mission ready and equipped forces (organized in effects-based operational capability packages) to deliver air, space, and
cyberspace capabilities to Joint commanders worldwide. DCAPES supports joint, combined, and DAF military operations worldwide.

FY 2027 funding will be used to support the continued development of capabilities within the DCAPES system. These efforts will enhance the Shortfall Management
Module which enables units to report and route manpower deficiencies to appropriate command level for resolution. The funding will also be used to develop the
Manpower Analysis Tool used to analyze and inform personnel planning and prevent future shortfalls.

The FY 2027 funding continues to enhance the functionality of the system, crucial in supporting war planning, and will be executed against capabilities packaged into
agile development projects for multiple releases based on warfighter priorities.

This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: DCAPES Continuous Development                                                                                                        8.154             8.390       5.254
Description: DCAPES Continuous Development Infrastructure Support, Business Intelligence, and the development of multiple
Warfighter requirements.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to enhance the Manpower Equipment and Force Packaging (MEFPAK) Module by developing Transportation and
Load Planning Data Creation, standardizing Manpower Force Element Line Numbers, and creating Air Force Specialty Code
Substitution Rules
- Create Force Presentation module that will present Force Apportionment and Assignment data
- Continue to develop/deploy additional user requirements, functionalities, and enhancements of the system
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue to enhance the Shortfall Module Update
- Will develop the Manpower Analysis Tool

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                FY 2025      FY 2026         FY 2027
- Will continue to develop/deploy additional user requirements, functionalities, and enhancements of the system
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding decreased to align with the program's migration schedule of moving the test, training, and production
environments to the Secret Internet Protocol Router Network (SIPR) cloud.
                                                                               Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals               8.154           8.390       5.254$$, $$$$, $$In Q1 FY 2025 the Deliberate Crisis Action Planning & Execution System (DCAPES) program completed Increment 2B full deployment and transitioned to the Software
Acquisition Pathway (SWP).

As a SWP program, DCAPES develops and sustains capabilities in accordance with the selected Agile software methodology to provide rapid development and delivery
of capabilities based on the warfighter's top priorities. The Program Management Office (PMO) maintains a backlog of requirements, and the stakeholders will verify
needs in an approved annual Capability Needs Statement (CNS) and project capabilities for an additional two years.

The contracting strategy is a FAR 16.505 Fair Opportunity task order off of the Small Business Enterprise Application Services (SBEAS) IDIQ contract.

The DCAPES PMO uses a mix of agreements (Service Level Agreements and Memorandums) with DCAPES interface partners. Memorandums of Agreement (MOA)
with Joint Interoperability Test Command (JITC) and the 45th Test Squadron are in place and outline the test support required before fielding the final capability
packages.

Program management for the DCAPES program is under direction of Program Executive Office (PEO) Business Enterprise Systems (BES), located at Gunter Annex
AFB, AL. The Air Force Life Cycle Management Center (AFLCMC) located at Gunter Annex AFB, AL provides contracting, legal, comptroller, programmatic, engineering,
test, and logistics support.

