C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Aircraft-Store Certification                                                                                                         3.894       3.125         4.125
Description: Evaluates aircraft-store compatibility through analysis of ground and flight test data. Supports procurement of test
assets, such as instrumented weapons, and includes end-to-end tracking of MAJCOM requirements from user request to tech
data fielding and operational flight program (OFP) updates. Provides certification recommendations to airworthiness authorities.

FY 2026 Plans:
-Continue to provide for USAF Air-to-Air and Air-to-Ground Munitions certification efforts, including towed decoys, ECM pods,
chaff/flare countermeasures certification efforts, Airborne Instrumentation Systems pods, fuel tanks, and travel pods certification
efforts. Efforts also include capability expansion on multiple aircraft for MALD, JASSM, APKWS, AIM-9x, AIM-120, and SDB II.
-Continue to provide CWDS upgrade support, Safe Escape software updates and Safe Separation Time Data.
FY 2027 Plans:
Support USAF Air-to-Air and Air-to-Ground Munitions certification by prioritizing the procurement of test assets for developmental
and operational testing, such as ground tests for electromagnetic compatibility and flight tests for separations.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
General inflation increase and mission growth.
Title: Operations Baseline and Mission Support                                                                                            22.840       22.517         23.758
Description: Supports the ability to rapidly meet emerging warfighter needs for global operations and other ongoing world-wide
operations through sustainment of a viable Air Force aircraft-store certification capability.

FY 2026 Plans:
-Continue to support increased Air Force munition and aircraft capability requirements that drive infrastructure and resource
capacity needs within the SEEK EAGLE enterprise.
FY 2027 Plans:
Sustain a viable Air Force aircraft-store certification capability by supporting increased Air Force munition and aircraft capability
requirements.
