E. Acquisition Strategy
The SEEK EAGLE program is not an acquisition program in itself; instead it supports other acquisition programs, for both aircraft and weapons or other stores. For
initial aircraft-weapons integration, the aircraft or weapon program office is responsible for budgeting and providing the test assets to the Air Force SEEK EAGLE Office
(AFSEO) for the store certification requirements. For post-integration certification requirements, AFSEO funds are used to obtain the non-inventory test assets. In
addition to the above highlights, budgeting responsibilities for AFSEO are delineated in Air Force Instruction 63-101/20-101, paragraph 5.4.22.1.3, dated 30 June 2020.




